description:
Soarin's life has always been horse hell. Twilight burning down Braeburn's farm and destroying their relationship was simply the last straw. Upon realizing he is now just a 50 y/o loner with no real life experiences outside of flying, Soarin returns to Ponyville to exact his revenge all all those who wronged him... with his newly awakened alicorn powers.
https://x.com/TheTamers12345
https://www.patreon.com/Tamers12345

Featuring an amazing original song written by some really cool and talented pony musicians!! ‪@princewhateverer‬, ‪@MelodyBrony‬, & ‪@dbponymusic‬ 
Check them out and give them a follow
https://x.com/PWhateverer
https://x.com/MelodyBrony

comments.text: This movie franchise really hit hard. Watching Soarin and Braeburn fight for their love in a world that won’t accept them was heartbreaking. Celestia’s cruelty—pushing them away just because they’re different—was so painful to see, especially from someone who’s supposed to embody wisdom and kindness. And Twilight… seeing her burn down Braeburn’s farm was devastating. That farm was his whole life, his dreams, his safe place, and she destroyed it without a second thought. The pain in their eyes, the loss, and then Soarin’s determination to stand up for what they have—it was raw and powerful. He deserved his chance at justice. This story reminds us that love deserves respect, no matter who it’s between, and sometimes you have to fight to protect it.
